commit.message:
Merge pull request #17 from adelosa/fix-windows-support

Fix to support Windows
Drop py2.6, 3.2 and 3.3 support. Add py3.6 support

Merge pull request #14 from ju2wheels/feature/centos_rhel_pg_path

Add CentOS/RHEL postgesql home directory blob to search patterns.
Updates py26 to use 2.6.0 version of flake8. Py26 +Windows is broken.
Merged in skip of tests containing os.fork for Window from windows _support branch.

Fix to support Windows (tk0miya/testing.postgresql#16)

* Assumes all other platforms work with sigint instead of sigterm
* testcases are broken on Windows due to use of os.fork
Add CentOS/RHEL postgesql home directory blob to search patterns.

Do not test for py32 on Travis CI

pip drops support for py32 since its version 8.0. So we cannot test it on Travis CI
Remove Postgresql#__getattr__(); Use self.settings instead of the accessor
Assign port to database server at testing.common.database
Move Postgresql#stop(), terminate() and cleanup() to testing.common.database
Rename options of PostgresqlFactory: cache_initialized_db and on_initizlied
